This paper proposes a novel Bayesian treatment of neural networks, which is a popular topic in the machine learning community. The paper focuses on the use of arbitrary exponential-family distributions to model the weights and neurons, which is related to topics such as probabilistic graphical models and statistical inference. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
